The paper deals with the problem of defining and extracting information content from images, which is a core topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The approach is based on the theory of information and complexity, which suggests that the information content of an image can be represented as a set of descriptions of its data structures. This involves techniques from information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG), as well as image processing and analysis (cs.MM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
